{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "d9f35a98-7bd5-4ddf-92db-a599bcf8f0cb",
    "name": "s3-proxy production verification",
    "description": "Postman collection for end-to-end verification of the s3-proxy business flow on staging or production.\n\nHow to use:\n1. Fill `baseUrl`, `apiKey`, and both backend account variable groups before running.\n2. Run the collection from top to bottom. The first request resets run-specific bucket/object names so each run is isolated.\n3. The collection bulk-imports two backend accounts, verifies multi-account placement using `/admin/accounts` `usedBytes`, tests core S3 flows (`PUT`, `GET`, `HEAD`, `LIST`, `DELETE`, logical bucket create/delete), and covers both multipart complete and multipart abort.\n4. Cleanup removes the logical bucket and all test objects, but it does not remove the imported backend accounts.\n\nImportant notes:\n- The proxy selects the least-used active account below `QUOTA_THRESHOLD`; it is not strict round-robin.\n- The default `usedBytes` and payload sizes are chosen so object 1 should land on `account01` and object 2 should land on `account02`.\n- In production, `POST /admin/accounts/import` should normally return `rtdbSynced=true`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      {
        "key": "key",
        "value": "x-api-key",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "value",
        "value": "{{apiKey}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "in",
        "value": "header",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
